Target: OntOvertopping is an ontology developed for representing wave conditions and overtopping discharge in coastal and port environments.

Comment: One of a series of ridges that moves across the surface of a liquid (especially across a large body of water) [EN Wordnet]
Label: Wave

Comment: The characteristics of a wave, such as wave height, period, angle and direction.
Label: WaveCondition

Comment: A structure built in coastal areas to protect entities such as ports, roads, railways, and their associated services from the impacts of waves, tides, and flooding.
Label: CoastalDefenceStructure

Comment: A wall constructed landward of the crest, functioning as part of a breakwater structure.
Label: CrestWall

Comment: The vertical distance between the base (toe) of a breakwater and the average height of the most energetic portion of the wave spectrum attacking the breakwater.
Label: SignificantWaveHeight

Comment: The vertical distance between the still water level (i.e., the water surface under calm conditions) and the seabed at the toe (base) of a breakwater.
Label: WaterDepthAtToeOfBreakwater

Comment: The horizontal distance across the base (toe) of a breakwater, measured from its landward edge to its seaward edge.
Label: WidthOfToe

Comment: A coefficient representing the influence of surface texture and structural features of a breakwater on the dissipation of wave energy.
Label: RoughnessCoefficient

Comment: The inclination angle of the slope located just above and adjacent to the base (toe) of a breakwater.
Label: AngleOfDownSlope

Comment: The inclination angle of the slope located just below and adjacent to the armour of a breakwater.
Label: AngleOfUpperSlope

Comment: The vertical distance between the still water level (SWL) and the crest of a breakwater.
Label: CrestFreeboardRelativeToSWL

Comment: The horizontal distance across the gently sloping section of a breakwater, typically located between the down slope and the upper slope.
Label: BermWidth

Comment: The vertical distance between the lowest elevation point of the berm and the still water level (SWL) in front of a breakwater.
Label: WaterDepthOnBerm

Comment: The inclination angle of the berm surface, typically measured relative to the horizontal plane.
Label: BermSlope

Comment: The vertical distance between the crest of the armour layer of a breakwater and the still water level (SWL).
Label: ArmourFreeboardRelativeToSWL

Comment: The horizontal thickness of the armour layer on a breakwater.
Label: ArmourWidth

Comment: The time interval between two successive wave crests passing a fixed point, such as a crest wall.
Label: WavePeriod

Comment: The compass direction from which the waves are coming, typically measured in degrees clockwise from true north (0°–360°).
Label: WaveDirection

Comment: The angle between the incoming wave direction and a specific structure or shoreline orientation, usually measured relative to the normal (perpendicular) to that structure.
Label: WaveAngle

Comment: A derived quantity indicating the volume of water per unit time that flows over a breakwater or crest wall due to wave action.
Label: OvertoppingDischarge

Comment: A quantity computed from a combination of other input parameters or measurements, rather than being directly observed.
Label: DerivedQuantity

Comment: The angle between the normal to the coastal or breakwater structure and the direction of the incident wave approach.
Label: WaveAttackAngle

Comment: An object property relating an instance of OvertoppingDischarge to the physical structure, e.g., a breakwater or crest wall, where the overtopping event occurs.
Label: happensAt

Comment: An object property that relates a CoastalDefenceStructure to one of its structural components, such as a CrestWall.
Label: hasPart

Comment: An object property referring to the measured value of a quantity.
Label: hasValue

Comment: An object property referring to the unit associated with a measured value.
Label: hasUnit

Comment: Relates a wave to its associated WaveCondition (e.g., height, period, angle and direction).
Label: hasWaveCondition

Comment: Relates a wave to the CoastalDefenceStructure that it impacts or overtops.
Label: attacks

Comment: Relates a wave to the WaveAttackAngle, representing the angle it forms with the CrestWall.
Label: hasAttackAngle

Comment: Relates the WaveAttackAngle to the CrestWall that serves as the reference structure for the angle measurement.
Label: isMeasuredAgainst

Comment: The numerical value of a measured quantity.
Label: hasNumericalValue
